# Prettier ignore — mirrors the `ignores` in .markdownlint-cli2.jsonc.
#
# These paths are generated artifacts, Agent Handoff state, or formatter-external
# contracts. Formatting them is churn or would conflict with their owning tool.
#
# Authored design docs under docs/superpowers/{specs,plans} are deliberately NOT
# ignored — they stay gated, same as markdownlint. Prettier already honors
# .gitignore, so .venv/ and caches need no entry here.
docs/codex-reviews/
docs/handoff/
tests/fixtures/specs/
tests/fixtures/package_compatibility/legacy/

# Agent Handoff owns exact managed blocks in the instruction files; its shape
# policy owns the status/task documents and preserves user-authored task wrapping.
AGENTS.md
CLAUDE.md
.agents/agent-handoff/
docs/STATUS.md
docs/TODO.md

# Machine-generated JSON Schema: its canonical byte format is owned by the
# standard_manifest.standard_schema_json() writer and enforced by a byte-drift
# test (json.dumps indent=2, key order preserved). Prettier's JSON style (inline
# short arrays) diverges from that, so letting Prettier own it would create a
# two-master conflict with the drift test. Hand-authored schemas stay gated.
src/project_standards/schemas/standard.schema.json
src/project_standards/schemas/standard-family.schema.json
src/project_standards/schemas/standard-payload.schema.json
src/project_standards/schemas/standards-catalog-source.schema.json
src/project_standards/schemas/consumer-catalog.schema.json
src/project_standards/schemas/consumer-config.schema.json
src/project_standards/schemas/consumer-lock.schema.json
src/project_standards/schemas/mutation-plan.schema.json
src/project_standards/schemas/provider-input.schema.json
src/project_standards/schemas/reconciliation-plan.schema.json
src/project_standards/schemas/migration-report.schema.json
standards/*/versions/*/schemas/mutation-plan.schema.json

# Package-contract fixtures are integrity inputs: their exact raw bytes and
# declared digests are one test contract, not formatter-owned source documents.
tests/fixtures/package_contract/

# Control-plane parser fixtures intentionally preserve consumer formatting,
# malformed syntax, duplicate keys, and other bytes that Prettier must not own.
tests/control_plane/fixtures/

# Manifest-generated catalog: the Python renderer and its checked-in freshness
# test own the exact bytes, so formatting it would create a second generator.
standards/catalog.md
